Seller's Description and Comments

This 1987 Fiero GT is in amazing condition. Rebuilt engine ~ it drives great and has much more power than your average Fiero. The body is flawless and the original paint is good for its age (you can see in the pictures how reflective the paint still is as it is reflecting the trees in the back ground and even the white lines from the parking lot). The motor runs and sounds great (as perfect as this car looks, the engine is the gem of the car). I am the type of person who is skeptic of any after market work done to any car I buy, especially of an engine that has been re-done. This car was not re-done because it was broken down....it was redone to make it better than your average Fiero and done right. I took it in to Gaynor's Automotive (A premium Shop here in Vancouver) and they actually opened it up and did a complete inpsection and said whoever did this engine did it right, and the car sounds like it! It is a 2800 V6 bored 30-over with forged pistons with a 5 speed transmission. It has roller rocker arms, a crane cam shaft, ported-heads, and a Holley Fuel Injection System. A new cat converter was installed so it passed with flying colors through WA DEQ which cost me $700. I looked for the perfect Fiero for almost 2 years and found this one in Detroit in 2010. The only time this car has ever been driven in the rain was when I drove it home from Detroit, and it drove great! It is currently licensed in WA State. It has a K&N Air Filter and custom dual-quad exhaust. The odometer reads 130,827 but the previous owner rebuilt the engine about 43,000 miles ago. He also did all of the modifications listed above. 

It has been kept in my garage since 2010 and the previous owner owned thi car since the early 90s and babied it more than his kids. From the time he owned it and as long as I have, it has always been garage kept. The clutch and plugs were recently replaced and have less than 250 miles on them. The car has 4 wheel disc brakes. The front brakes have been checked and look great. The calipers in the rear are new along with the pads and one of the rotors. It has leather interior that is in great shape. The head lights are fully functional. It has Fiero-GT floor mats, and a 10 disc CD-changer. It also has the huge sun roof shown in the pictures. I have nearly all of the paperwork for the car from the early 90s until now. This Fiero is garaged (and covered) and has been meticulously cared for. 

And you will not have to worry about this car having body cracks or such issues that I have seen recenlty on another fiero here on Craigslist that was in this price range. Can't beleive someone is selling for about my price for their fiero (with low miles) with cracks?? Just because it has lower miles does not mean it is nicer.  The air condiitoning is perfect and ice cold ~ and brand new.....have receipts.  

If you drove one of these gowing up, you know how fun they are...and if you have not yet, you are truly missing out. 

I have over 10k into this car since 2010 and have receipts.  

We can meet at my FFL Dealer in Vancouver if we make a deal.

Best Cash Offer or nicest trade gets this Fiero GT.

postcontent:
This is a great opportunity to own a great deal of history.
Selling these relics on behalf of a collector, his personal notes and research will be included with each piece.

Up for sale are as follows:

1. Type 30 Arisaka Japanese bayonet handles (just handles)

2. 1907 British Enfield bayonet. Manufactured in 12/18, Dec 18. Made by the Wilkinson Sword Company. Shows two enfield royal small arms factory inspection stamps, as well as an X for bending mark, proof of blade.

3. India Bayonet MKI, Originally shortened from a British 1907 pattern.
Converted 3/43, March 1943 in RFI, Rifle factory Ishapore to MKII. There are three Ishapore inspection marks.

4. India Bayonet MKII. Manufactured in 11/44, November 1944. Was the last and crudest type manufactured as it was painted black among other small differences. It has three Ishapore inspection marks and a DP for Drill Proof

5. M1941 Spanish "Bolo" blade bayonet. Manufactured in Toledo, serial number 3198 P over 4, under side handle XXV both match.

6. Czechoslovakian Bayonet. Designed for czech version of the k98 Mauser, this is the long version. Reverse blade on guard has Z with a circle around it.
Has CSZ export marks, made in BRNO factory.

^ 6b. There are two Czechoslovakian bayonets like the one above in this lot.

7. Swiss Model 1889 WAFFENFABRIK NEUHAUSEN bayonet.
These were manufactured from 1889-1917. Under guard has swiss cross.
Nuehausen is a city near the german border, made for the Schmidt-Rubin rifle. Serial number 302917

8. Swedish M/96 bayonet. Made by rifle factory of Carl Gustafs town.
has C under a crown. Issued to rifle number 363, sheath made by Eskillstuna Jern Manufacturing Inc. Sent to Landstorm 4th Infantry, Landstormen District 23b, 4th Infantry number 103, includes leather frog

9. Swiss bayonet manufactured by Victorinox from 1950's to 1980's for the Sig rifle.

10. Belgian Army Pocket Knife from 1951. A.B.L. ( Arme'e Belge-belgisch leger colasse.

11. Same as number 10 only its the colin winanel version.  

12. M1889/98 Imperial German bayonet

title: For Trade:  M1A E2
postcontent: I have for sale a M1A E2. The M14 E2 was an attempt at a replacement for the BAR in Vietnam. As it was deployed late in the Vietnam war parts are becoming increasingly hard to come by. The M1A is Springfield's version of the M14. It sits in an unissued 1969 production birch E2 stock that is finished with tung oil. The stock's hardware is reproduction (original hardware simply no longer exists. I have searched for months to no avail). E2 stocks in this condition are very difficult to find, especially originals. It sports a Springfield M2 bipod, Fulton Armory National Match flash hider with bayonet lug, and fulton armory reproduction compensator that attaches over the flash hider (it does a great job at mitigating perceived recoil). To finish it off I added a 1973 production new in wrapper E2 sling. E2 slings are different from standard M14/M1A slings as they are longer and sport a clip for an optional forward handgrip. The Handguard is a slotted and vented fiberglass handguard that was issued in vietnam, but is considered in excellent condition. Will include a both a 25 round and a 10 round magazine. I'm open to negotiation on price and trades.
